Package edu.ncsu.csc216.ticket_manager.model.ticket

Class Ticket

  • java.lang.Object
    • edu.ncsu.csc216.ticket_manager.model.ticket.Ticket
  • public class Ticket
extends java.lang.Object
    Class that creates the Ticket object, which contains all the info for a ticket. Tickets are constructed assuming valid parameters. Tickets can also be updated or printed as a String for export.
    Author:
    Benson Liu

    • Constructor Detail

      • Ticket

        public Ticket​(int id,
              java.lang.String state,
              java.lang.String ticketType,
              java.lang.String subject,
              java.lang.String caller,
              java.lang.String category,
              java.lang.String priority,
              java.lang.String owner,
              java.lang.String code,
              java.util.ArrayList<java.lang.String> notes)
        One of two constructors for Ticket. Creates a Ticket when reading from a ticket file. Creates a Ticket object with ticket ID, state, type, subject, caller, category, priority, owner, code, and notes. An IllegalArgumentException is thrown in the setter methods if the parameters are not valid. If the incoming ID is greater than the current value in Ticket.counter, the Ticket.counter is updated with Ticket.setCounter(id + 1)
        Parameters:
        id - ID of ticket
        state - State of ticket
        ticketType - Type of ticket
        subject - Subject of ticket
        caller - Caller of ticket
        category - Category of ticket
        priority - Priority of ticket
        owner - Owner of ticket
        code - Code ticket
        notes - Notes for ticket

      • Ticket

        public Ticket​(Ticket.TicketType ticketType,
              java.lang.String subject,
              java.lang.String caller,
              Ticket.Category category,
              Ticket.Priority priority,
              java.lang.String note)
        One of two constructors for Ticket. Constructs a Ticket object with ticket type, subject, caller, category, priority, and notes. If any of the parameters are null or the strings are empty, an IllegalArgumentException is thrown. The ticketId is set to the value stored in the Ticket.counter field, then counter is incremented in the Ticket.incrementCounter() method. The owner field is initialized to an empty string, the other fields are initialized to their parameter values.
        Parameters:
        ticketType - Type of ticket
        subject - Subject of ticket
        caller - Caller of ticket
        category - Category of ticket
        priority - Priority of ticket
        note - Notes on ticket
